Direct Known Subclasses:
OsnBooleanConverter
public abstract class OsnBaseBooleanValueConverter
extends OsnFieldValueConverter

An abstract implementation of the OsnFieldValueConverter which narrows the scope of a conversion to ensure a boolean value is converted to. The convertBoolean method must be implemented by any subclass converter and the result must either be a boolean value or a thrown OsnConversionException if the conversion was not successful. The OSN Boolean Gadget Type requires that the values "T"/"F" be supplied signifying true/false. The convert method will take the result from convertBoolean and return either "T"/"F".

See OsnFieldValueConverter javadoc for more information on how to consume converters and the other override options.
